[SN]TITLE[SN]
Woman killed on A1 in East Lothian named by police

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
The family of a woman who died in a crash with a Ford Transit pick-up on the A1 near Dunbar in East Lothian said she "sparkled inside and out".

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
Meghan Ambrozevich-Blair, 26, from Dunbar, was driving northbound at about 07:50 on Friday when her black Kia Cerato collided with the truck.
The 54-year-old male pick-up driver was taken to hospital. His injuries were not thought to be life-threatening.
Ms Ambrozevich-Blair's family said they were "absolutely devastated".
They said: "This tragedy has robbed everyone of a future with such a loving, caring, kind, beautiful and happy person who sparkled inside and out.
"The outpouring of love we have received has both been of great comfort to her family and friends, and a testament to just how many lives she enhanced."
